gomodel:SYNGO_5051  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2, 3: Confocal imaging of cultured hippocampal neurons showed over-expression of IQGAP1 stimulated spine formation and increased spine head size. The effect was strongly reduced in an IQGAP1 mutant lacking the CHD domain.\n\nFigure 5: IQGAP1 mutants that lacks C-terminus also stimulates spine formation; deletion of this domain does not prevent the stimulatory effect of IQGAP1 on spine number or spine head size.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Embryonic day-18 rat embryos (euthanized by CO2 overdose) were used to prepare primary hippocampal cultures as previously described [35]-[40].\"\n\n\"For IQGAP1-sh\nForward: 5'TGCCATGGATGAGATTGGAAAGCTTTCCAATCTCATCCATGGCACTTTTTTG and.\nReverse: 5'AATTCAAAAAGTGCCATGGATGAGATTGGAAAGCTTTCCAATCTCATCCATGGCA.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5051" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

